reviewText: AN ESTONIAN GANGSTER FILM NO LESS!....AND I THINK SOME FILM STUDENTS IN A LOCAL HIGH SCHOOL MIGHT HAVE DONE BETTER
Good movie.  Interesting setting early in independence of Estonia.  If you forgive the outlandish plot, it's a fun movie.

The movie touch period after getting independence from much hated communistic parasite called Soviet Union. Done very professionally and realistically movie trying to show how life is really designed, how people live, lost, make mistakes and how they separated in classes. It also shows that criminals are a class in itself which is taboo topic everywhere. Excellent.
